        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/RatFunc.2EtoFractionRingAlgEquiv/near/511811737\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Maybe you should prove that if K[X] is an R-algebra then there's an R-algebra isomorphism between them</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>According to the results of my previous search for <code>RatFunc AlgEquiv</code> on the forum engine, perhaps <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"224323\">@Junyan Xu</span>  has already proved the conclusion of this enhanced version.</p>",
